// cb_syntax.md §1.1 — `\` at end of line fuses the lines unconditionally.
// The continuation MUST be transparent to the parser regardless of lexer
// trivia mode.

total = a + b + c + \
    d + e + f

// Continuation between operator and operand on consecutive lines.
sum = 1 \
    + 2 \
    + 3

// Continuation inside an argument list.
result = foo(a, \
    b, \
    c)

// Continuation between `Then` and the single-line body.
If x > 0 Then \
    y = 1
